physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Mrs C was fully dilated and saw her doctor who reported contractions at 2 1/2 minutes without her feeling them.
Apgar scores for baby Noelle were 1, 4, and 7 at 1, 5, and 10 minutes; severe respiratory distress syndrome confirmed by chest radiograph.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Initially intubated and given surfactant; extubated to continuous positive airway pressure on day 5.
Status improved sufficiently so by day 36, she was returned to enteral nutrition and slowly advanced.
